description: From translingual Paspalum, from Hellenistic Ancient Greek πάσπαλος (páspalos, “type of millet”).

entries.meaning: Any member of the genus Paspalum of tall perennial grasses, the bahiagrasses or Dallis grasses.
examples: We returned to the crossing, passing slowly through the high rusty stands of dock weeds and the fleshy beds of dense paspalum.
